  <name>LinuxPop</name>
  <summary>A floating popup of context-aware actions for selected text</summary>

  <description>
    <p>
      LinuxPop watches the text you select on screen and surfaces a small
      floating popup with relevant actions: search the web, copy to clipboard,
      open URLs and paths, send to your favourite AI assistant, encode/decode
      common formats, translate, run quick scripts. Inspired by PopClip on
      macOS, built for Linux - on X11 and on KDE Plasma 6 / Wayland.
    </p>
    <p>Highlights:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Floating action popup that appears at your text selection</li>
      <li>Runs on both X11 and KDE Plasma 6 / Wayland</li>
      <li>Context-aware buttons (URL decode only shows on encoded URLs, etc.)</li>
      <li>Send any selection to ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity or local Ollama</li>
      <li>In-place translation bubble with a language picker</li>
      <li>Clipboard manager + snippets picker on a configurable hotkey</li>
      <li>No-code recipe wizard for building your own custom buttons</li>
      <li>Plugin marketplace with one-click install of community actions</li>
      <li>Light and premium dark themes</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

